# Global Protocol: youtube-transcript-notes

## Initialization

- Any non-trivial task starts by reading `.cursor/brain/PROJECT_CONTEXT.md`.
- If the task touches workflow, artifacts, prompt assembly, or transcript generation, also read `.cursor/brain/MAP.md`, `.cursor/brain/SKELETONS.md`, and `.cursor/brain/DECISIONS.md`.
- `.cursor/brain/` is the local source of truth for this repository.

## Language

- Russian for chat.
- English for code, comments, filenames, docs, and rule content.

## Repository Hygiene

- Keep the project local-first. Do not switch the default flow to an external MCP or remote API unless the user explicitly asks.
- No generated files in the repo root. Generated workflow outputs belong under `artifacts/videos/`.
- Do not keep stale workflow files, duplicate rules, or outdated docs when the canonical path changes.
